    "body": "I could be coming way out of left field on this one but were metaclasses ever given consideration for the accessors? It seems like using them instead of decorators would still allow you to register the methods you need on a subclass, but at the same time give give you access to that registered metadata without having to store it in a private variable in the subclass"
